"name": "kliewerje"
},
"reviewBody": "I made this in a cast iron Dutch oven. I drained the grease off of the ground beef and sautéed fresh garlic instead of granulated. I used two pint jars (32oz total) of homemade cherry tomato sauce. Served it with a side salad, garlic bread would be great with it as well. This recipe is an excellent starting point and easily customizable. The next time I make it, I’ll incorporate chopped onions and bell peppers. Everyone got seconds and my husband ate it for breakfast this morning."
}
